We visited Cha Da tonight for the first time and it was delicious!
We ordered the yellow curry, the jasmine fried rice, and pad thai.
We started with Tom Kha soup, which was amazing!
The yellow curry was extremely tasty, flavored with coconut milk and just the right consistency.
The pad thai comes with chicken and shrimp, and the flavor was spot on.
There are two versions of the jasmine fried rice - spicy and not spicy.
We tried the not spicy version and adjusted the heat with different sauces available.
The staff was very friendly, and we even received a lesson on the origin of the restaurant's name.
We had a great experience at Cha Da Thai and will definitely be going back - soon!

